review_blob: Pours cloudy gold. Orange runs around your mouth and pulls some coriander along for the ride. I sat in a corner of a dark pub in NYC, sipping these with my coworker. It was a very hot day, and an emotional one that we were glad to get behind us. Tipping back a few of these helped ease my mind a bit. The balance of flavors was very calming on a sticky day.

Snagged one of them big ass bottles and popped it Labor Day. Nice color, interesting and slightly funky smell. Goes down well but a tart berry aftertaste caught me off guard. Its like a moldy Strawberry burrowed out the ground, made its way up my body and hopped in my mouth at as soon as I took a swig. Attempted to muscle through it but it began to get on my nerves. I let it get warm on the table, lost in the shuffle of the BBQ.

Golden yellow, slight aroma of lime. Had some at the bar, and each time someone ordered one, we got a resounding NO! when we asked them if they wanted another for the next round. Tastes like someone was  trying to ferment Pellegrino. Avoid at all costs.

The beer to have when youre having more than one. Tastes of corn and unwashed underwear. I assume its gold. I mean,  Its Schaefers, what am I going to pour it out of the can for? A few years back a buddy and myself ran through a 24 pack he got for about $6 as we watched the MLB playoffs all day and night. We dubbed it Bad Beer Night and bought the worst things we could drink for shits and giggles. As we drank on it became laborious, but we chugged on, laughing at the fact that we were tearing though a 24 of Schaefer. Not for the faint of heart.

Old Badass Reliable. Dark body, head that stays with you. The only failsafe for real drinkers when they cant decide what to get. Whether youre out and about on a Friday night or at the pub watching footie early in the morning, you cant miss with this one. For Strength.

As soon as you pop the cap a green apple shoots up at you and into your lungs. Pours a hazy gold, white head which melts in a heartbeat. Tastes likes an aroma that would invade your senses, when you taste a smell, as if you sat at the kitchen table watching your grandmother slice green apples into an apple pie. Beautiful. Honey aftertaste is brilliant.

Its like the ghost made of corn and water flew up my nose. A bit skunky, watery, and bland. Anyone who tries to pair this with a nice Italian dinner is fooling themselves (besides, what are you drinking beer at a nice Italian dinner for anyway? You should be drinking wine). Not the worst but youre not missing anything.

I tipped back bottles of these in London before a Football match. Slightly floral aroma, yellow color. Crisp flavor, a bit watery, but still a clean flavor. Decent and enjoyable. When I grabbed some here in the States my idiot friends lambasted me for drinking a French Beer, and drawing that kind of stupidity out of morons ups the rating a bit.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Tap. gold color, white head. Nice fruity aroma, but the apricot flavor is a bit too strong for my liking. Ill save that sort of intensity for fruit tarts and jams. Apricot aftertaste makes me yearn for a shot of Jameson afterwards, which may not be a bad thing depending on the setting. Give this to a date who doesnt want to drink heavy beers.

Bottle. Not that bad, thought not the best Pumpkin Ale Ive had. Subtle flavors, which isnt a bad thing, really. A Pumpkin Ale isnt supposed to taste like youre sticking your face into a Pumpkin Pie. Aroma was quite lacking though.
beer_name: Blue Moon Harvest Moon Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: I tore off the label on a Coors Light bottle once and it said Poland Spring underneath. The beer fat guys drink in large quantities because they think it wont make them fatter.  If thats all you got at a party, leave because that party probably sucks. Only positive is if you live in New Jersey because Jersey girls live off this shit and that will help your prospects of getting some.

Solid cheap beer, even though hipsters have caught onto it. I spent a good 15 years drinking these in the park across the street from Yankee Stadium, where the new one is being built now. Drank them fast too, because as soon as it gets slightly warm its vile. Yet, ice cold it reminds me of the Summertime and stumbling into my section in the 3rd inning loaded and feeling great.

I remember boozing up to this before all the hipsters caught wind of it. *sigh* Those were the days. Looks, smells and tastes like a cheap beer, and feels like you drank a brick, yet theres something wonderfully charming about it when youre in a smelly dive bar 3:30 in the morning and you know the $20 bucks you have left can get you 3 more beers and a cab ride home.

Bottle. Pours black as Satans heart with a wonderfully inviting tan head that tells you right away you are going to get a kick in the sack if youre some pansy drinker. Felt like I was having sex with a Victorias Secret model who tasted of roasted coffee and chocolate. Fantastic beer.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle. Piss yellow with a terrible excuse for a head. Tastes and smells like I had sex with a 90 year old women who died six hours earlier. Im sure if you poured this over grass your lawn would brown wilt and  after a few hours.

Bottle. Piss yellow, smells like you wont enjoy it, tastes like it also, but add a lime and the dimension changes slightly. Inviting bottle reminds me of drunken BBQs. If thats all thats available youll live.
